import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='size', kde=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title("What is the distribution of the size of the nodes in the flare.json dataset?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.title("What is the relationship between the depth and the size of the nodes in the flare.json dataset?", wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;
